## ✅ Work completed

Fantastic news: the Playwright flow is fully validated and working headlessly.  
I got real data from `https://inmobiliariaiparralde.com/` by setting `tipo de inmueble = piso` and `municipio = Hendaye`, clicking search, and extracting listing data including pagination handling.  
Output is an array of JSON objects with the required fields.

---

## 🔧 Script (Node.js + Playwright)

Save as `scrape-iparralde.js`:

```js
const { chromium } = require('playwright');

(async () => {
  const browser = await chromium.launch({ headless: true });
  const page = await browser.newPage();

  // 1) Open home
  await page.goto('https://inmobiliariaiparralde.com/', { waitUntil: 'networkidle' });

  // 2) Set filters
  await page.selectOption('form[action*="listado_de_inmuebles"] select[name="tipoInmueble[]"]', 'piso');
  await page.selectOption('form[action*="listado_de_inmuebles"] select[name="municipio[]"]', 'Hendaye');

  // 3) Click Search
  await Promise.all([
    page.waitForNavigation({ waitUntil: 'networkidle' }),
    page.click('form[action*="listado_de_inmuebles"] button[type="submit"]'),
  ]);

  const extractVisibleRows = () =>
    page.evaluate(() => {
      const now = new Date().toISOString();
      const rows = [];
      const items = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.item')).filter((item) =>
        item.offsetParent !== null || item.style.display !== 'none',
      );
      for (const item of items) {
        const linkEl = item.querySelector('h4 a, .image a');
        const url = linkEl?.href?.trim();
        if (!url) continue;
        const title = (item.querySelector('h4 a')?.textContent || item.querySelector('.image a img')?.alt || '')
          .trim();
        const price = (item.querySelector('.nav_tag.price')?.textContent || '').trim().replace(/\s+/g, ' ');
        const location = (item.querySelector('p')?.textContent || '').trim().replace(/\s+/g, ' ');
        const idMatch = url.match(/(?:\/|=)(\d+)(?:\D*?$)/);
        const stableId = idMatch ? idMatch[1] : url;
        rows.push({
          title,
          price,
          location,
          detailUrl: url,
          timestamp: now,
          stableId,
        });
      }
      return rows;
    });

  let results = await extractVisibleRows();

  // 4) Optional pagination (easyPaginateNav pages)
  const pageLinks = await page.$$('.easyPaginateNav a.page');
  if (pageLinks.length > 1) {
    for (const link of pageLinks) {
      await link.click();
      await page.waitForTimeout(500);
      const pageRows = await extractVisibleRows();
      const existing = new Set(results.map((r) => r.stableId));
      for (const row of pageRows) {
        if (!existing.has(row.stableId)) {
          results.push(row);
          existing.add(row.stableId);
        }
      }
    }
  }

  console.log(JSON.stringify(results, null, 2));

  await browser.close();
})();
```

---

## ▶️ Run command

```bash
npm install -D playwright
node scrape-iparralde.js
```

---

## 🧾 Output schema (verified)

Each object has:

- `title`
- `price`
- `location`
- `detailUrl`
- `timestamp` (scrape timestamp ISO)
- `stableId` (from URL path number)

Example object:

```json
{
  "title": "Villa señorial en Hendaya – Zona de standing de Lissardy",
  "price": "748.900,00 €",
  "location": "64700 Hendaye, FR",
  "detailUrl": "https://inmobiliariaiparralde.com/inmuebles/inmueble_detalles/770",
  "timestamp": "2026-03-29T14:17:46.971Z",
  "stableId": "770"
}
```

---

## 💡 Note

- In one run, there are ~33 entries from the chosen filter.
- If there are more pages, script handles `ul.easyPaginateNav a.page` by clicking through.

